snippet.textDisplay:
Intel has the supply/production capacity to meet enterprise demand so they are going to keep the lions share of the market. AMD might be winning the actual performance battle but they won't be able to beat Intel until they can scale up, which won't happen overnight. 

The ideal scenario for "prosumers" is for AMD to keep beating Intel on performance but with Intel keeping its majority market share so AMD has to keep undercutting Intel on price. 

If AMD actually got comparable market share with Intel, it would suck from a gamer/"enthusiast" perspective as they would inevitably start raising margins and reducing the price/performance ratio of their products. If it completely trounces Intel in terms of market share it would do what Intel has been doing for the past few generations, i.e. basically price gouge consumers.
